title: $:/plugins/tiddlywiki/codemirror-6-collab-nwjs/readme

This plugin adds //real-time collaborative editing// to TiddlyDesktop. Open the same room from
several TiddlyDesktop instances and tiddlers you share are kept in sync as you type, with live
cursors in the CodeMirror 6 editor.

!! What you get

* ''Live co-editing'' — shared tiddlers synchronise character-by-character using [[Yjs|https://github.com/yjs/yjs]] CRDTs, with remote cursors and selections shown in the CodeMirror 6 editor.
* ''Per-tiddler sharing'' — share just the tiddlers you choose (toolbar share button); others in the room see them in the //Get// panel and can subscribe. The first peer to share a title owns it.
* ''Attachments'' — shared image/binary tiddlers stream peer-to-peer (paced under the relay's limit); each is saved as an external file or embedded according to your External Attachments setting.
* ''Chat'' — a room chat panel, including private 1:1 messages, with an optional notification sound.
* ''Conflict-safe'' — offline or concurrent edits are detected against a 3-way base; genuine divergences are flagged and resolved with a diff/merge dialog rather than silently overwriting.
* ''End-to-end encryption'' — generating an invite mints a room token (shared out of band, never sent to the relay) so room traffic is encrypted; peer identities are authenticated via relay-signed membership certificates.

!! How it connects

* A ''WebSocket relay'' carries traffic between instances on different networks. Set its URL in the collaboration settings and sign in (GitHub / GitLab / OIDC) to authenticate.
* On the ''same LAN'', instances also connect directly (lower latency), unless //Relay only// is enabled.
* Share a room by generating an ''invite code'' and sending it to a collaborator out of band; applying it joins the room (and, with the embedded token, enables end-to-end encryption).

!! Notes

* Executable tiddlers (JavaScript, raw markup, plugins) are never accepted from peers, and your own collaboration/security configuration can never be overwritten by a peer.
* System (`$:/`) tiddlers are only shared/received when you opt in via //Allow system tiddlers//.
* This plugin is specific to TiddlyDesktop (NW.js); it relies on the desktop app's networking and is not intended for a browser-hosted wiki.
